Lagos bound Mass Transit Train had a head-on collision with a truck in Iju/Fagba area of Lagos causing a heavy gridlock. The incident reportedly occurred at about 8.52 am around Mofolasayo Drive, Jonathan Coker Road Level Crossing, Fagba. There were no reports of casualties recorded at the scene as of 10.30am, but it was gathered that law enforcement officials and other emergency responders were on the ground to attend to the situation. Eyewitnessesâ€™ account said the incident disrupted the free flow of traffic in the axis as traffic was swiftly diverted to alternative routes to ease the worries of motorists and commuters.